# CredentialManager

The Credential Management in the library is built upon the Vault API.

It's initiated by passing along the Vault API key for the desired credentials list.

## Manager Creation

### API

```
from wcp_library.credentials.api import APICredentialManager

CredentialsManager = APICredentialManager(<API_KEY>)
```

### FTP/SFTP

```
from wcp_library.credentials.ftp import FTPCredentialManager

CredentialsManager = FTPCredentialManager(<API_KEY>)
```

### Internet

```
from wcp_library.credentials.internet import InternetCredentialManager

CredentialsManager = InternetCredentialManager(<API_KEY>)
```

### Oracle

```
from wcp_library.credentials.oracle import OracleCredentialManager

CredentialsManager = OracleCredentialManager(<API_KEY>)
```

### Postgres

```
from wcp_library.credentials.postgres import PostgresCredentialManager

CredentialsManager = PostgresCredentialManager(<API_KEY>)
```

## Methods
### get_credentials

`def get_credentials(self, username: str) -> dict:`

Get credentials [returns](https://github.com/Whitecap-DNA/WCP-Library/wiki/Credentials-%E2%80%90-Expected-Dictionaries) the credentials for the requested username.

```
credentials = CredentialsManager.get_credentials(<username>)
```

### get_credential_from_id

`def get_credential_from_id(self, password_id: int) -> dict:`

Get credentials [returns](https://github.com/Whitecap-DNA/WCP-Library/wiki/Credentials-%E2%80%90-Expected-Dictionaries) the credentials for the requested passwordID.

```
credentials = CredentialsManager.get_credential_from_id(<passwordID>)
```

### update_credential

`def update_credential(self, credentials_dict: dict) -> bool:`

Update credentials is used to update existing entries in Password State (the Vault), with whatever is passed to the function.

The return boolean is an indicator on successful update with the Vault.

```
existing_credentials = CredentialsManager.get_credentials(<username>)

new_credentials = copy.deepcopy(existing_credentials)
new_credentials['Password'] = "Test-Example"

success_state = CredentialsManager.update_credential(new_credentials)

if success_state == True:
    print("The password was successfully updated.")
else:
    print("The password update failed.")
```

### new_credentials

`def new_credentials(self, credentials_dict: dict) -> bool:`

New credentials creates a new password entry within Password State (the Vault)

The credentials_dict [parameter](https://github.com/Whitecap-DNA/WCP-Library/wiki/Credentials-%E2%80%90-Expected-Dictionaries) is required.

It's essentially easier to get an existing credential using [get_credential()](https://github.com/Whitecap-DNA/WCP-Library/wiki/Credentials-%E2%80%90-Synchronous#get_credentials) and modifying it to contain the new passwords information.

The return boolean is an indicator on successful entry with the Vault.

```
existing_credentials = CredentialsManager.get_credentials(<username>)

new_credentials = copy.deepcopy(existing_credentials)
new_credentials['UserName'] = "Test-User-Example"
new_credentials['Password'] = "Test-Pass-Example"
new_credentials['Notes'] = "This is a test connection for the wiki"

success_state = CredentialsManager.new_credential(new_credentials)

if success_state == True:
    print("The password was successfully saved in the Vault.")
else:
    print("The password entry failed.")
```